    An object which may be written to and read from a ByteBuffer.

    • Method Detail

      • getWireLength

        @Nonnegative
int getWireLength(@Nonnull
                            IpmiPacketContext context)
        Returns the wire length of this packet. This must be exact, and not an overestimate. If #toWire(IpmiContext, java.nio.ByteBuffer) writes fewer bytes than the computed length, the base class will assume error in the serializer and throw an exception. It is generally not valid to call getWireLength() on a Wireable which does not contain complete data, as the length of data-dependent fields cannot be computed.
